06:00 I wonder why u guys didnt take the Kaghan route?
It is shorter in distance and a lot quicker.
Moreover you bet to pass through Naran, the most visited tourist destination in Pakistan. And u could see in Naran ..Legendary Lake Saiful Malook at 10,700ft above sea level... I bet u havent seen a lake any hogher than this

Then u pass by serene Lake Lulusar... then you elevate to a height of 13,691 feet at Babusar Pass (or "Top"), its twice as high as the highest pass in Canada.

It would have saved you hours
It takes almost the same time to get to Besham or Naran
But then, from naran to Chilas is 3 hrs.... and besham to chilas is 6 hours 40 min
so u probably save 3 hours of driving ... but the best thing is Naran route is way way way more scenic
Not to mention , it doesnt have that problem of "Landslides" that you have (and did) encounter on KKH
